abstract: Jewish Board of Family and Children’s Services, beneficiary of UJA-Federation of New York, uses $1,234 from New York Times Neediest Cases Fund to pay first month's rent at assisted-living community for Jinji Nicole, who was unable to walk after tumor caused trauma to her spine.
lead_paragraph: Jinji Nicole was told she might no longer walk because of trauma a tumor had done to her spine. She proved everyone wrong, including herself.

headline.main: Felled by Tumor, Model Finds Strength to Walk Again
headline.print_headline: After a Tumor, Finding the Strength to Walk Again
